Aug 7 2009 	Perfect London hotel for our family!	We researched many hotels to accomodate our family of 4 - two middle school kids. Wanted enough beds &amp; space to spread out. This was perfect. We had 2 &quot;living rooms&quot; &amp; a small kitchen, 2 bathrooms. I was a bit worried after reading some negative reviews - I can be a hotel &quot;snob&quot;. (Comments about stained carpet, which is due to be replaced this fall. They did shampoo it upon request) But, this hotel is a perfect London hotel. Very charming, great staff (Ahlam is the best!). Location is near great shopping &amp; tube. Staff anticipated our needs! Would recommend it to all my friends!	
Jul 24 2009 	Your very own Sloane street Pied-a-terre....	Durley house could quintessentially become my own Sloane street Pied-a terre! Impressive with its 11 beautiful rooms it remained a soothing calmness and air of a private house. I was delighted to be greated by such a warm welcome after battling against the awful english weather! And was even more delighted to enter a beautifully spacious apartment complete with a kitchen! If like me you need privacy and space but still need to remain in the heart of London city then Durley House is a perfect pied-a-terre to call your very own.....well at least for a little while...!	
Apr 24 2009 	Enjoy the space and location..great for families.	I had read very mixed reviews about this hotel, but for our family needs (2 adults, 2 young children) it was perfect. The hotel does look as if it hasn't been touched since the 1980's-it's a bit like a time warp, but I thought it had a good feel to it. Traditional English style - antiques, huge oil paintings of men with moustaches, dumb waiters (not the human type!), etc. Facilities good - taps in bathroom could do with a re-chrome, but it's made of sturdy stuff - it's the actual space that we valued above all.. Staff very helpful and not intrusive. If you're into minimalist perfection and shiney surfaces then this isn't the place for you...but if you're after a relaxed stay in a great location with lots of space then I would highly recommend it. We stayed in the Durley Suite... I loved the huge sitting room area - you could do several cartwheels here if you wanted (not that we did) - ceiling to floor windows overlooking cadogan private gardens. Staff can give you a key ( and tennis racquets) for the gardens (two tennis courts and a play area for younger children ). Harrods down the road and Kings Road round the corner. Would come back here.	
