Mar 17 2007	A little paradise in the heart of London	In the last few years , have been traveled a lot to the Uk. I have a decent inclination for sophistication and high standards and I admit I love english styles, traditional and modern.  I must disagree with some negative reviews I have seen lately about the Durley House Hotel in Sloane Street, London. I have stayed there for numerous times and I have found the place a little paradise of personalised service and friendlyness. In fact, I know that I have been literally a pain, in asking for help in different occasions and the staff and management was incredibly helpful and accurate. I can't count the times I have visited since last year and already 2007, but I can't wait for the opportunity to be able to bring my family and friends, as I have felt like home and would love to enjoy london with them in a place like this	
